# Supply-chain hardening: refuse to install any package version that's been
# on npm for less than 7 days. Catches malicious-version drops (Mini
# Shai-Hulud / TanStack 2026-05 etc.) since the npm community typically
# detects + de-lists within 24-72h.
#
# Mostly a defense-in-depth tripwire: `npm ci` from a pinned lockfile
# bypasses version resolution entirely, so this only fires on `npm install
# <new-pkg>` or `npm update`. Pairs with Dependabot cooldown:7 which guards
# the auto-bump path.
#
# Requires npm 11.10.0+. CI workflow needs `npm install -g npm@latest`
# before install if it hits version resolution.
min-release-age=7
